@fileoverview
Tooltip helpers for the Code Structure D3 renderer.

This module is intentionally framework-agnostic:
- Pure DOM operations (no dependency on Bootstrap)
- Can be used from classic <script> tags (no ESM required)

Usage (in d3_codeStructure.js):
  const tip = CodeStructure.tooltip.ensureTooltip();
  CodeStructure.tooltip.showTooltip(tip, event, htmlString);
  CodeStructure.tooltip.hideTooltip(tip);

Convert an absolute path to a root‑relative POSIX id.

Behavior
--------
1. Compute the relative path from `rootAbs` → `absPath`.
2. Reject paths that escape the root (".." segments).
3. Normalize separators to POSIX style so the UI receives stable ids.

This function intentionally returns `null` instead of throwing because
watcher events may occasionally produce paths outside the analyzed root
(symlinks, editor temp files, etc.).

@param {string} rootAbs
@param {string} absPath
@returns {string|null}
